Pastor Prince John Mpumechi, the General Oversees, Eagles Ministries, aka City of God, has called on every leader in Nigeria to embrace God’s tenets if they will work in divine wisdom. The cleric, who was speaking on activities leading to the coming general elections, maintained that without divine wisdom and understanding, the leaders would not handle the affairs of this country well. He maintained that the nation’s leaders had abandoned the Lord and now act according to their own personal knowledge to the detriment of the nation. 2023: Cleric Urges Politicians To Shun Do-Or-Die Politics Ending Domestic Violence, Bias Against Women Mpumechi urged leaders to draw close to the Lord so they could be agents of peace and development, unlike what had been obtained in recent times.He said: “Youths in this country should wake up. They are the leaders of tomorrows. The youths should shun evil ways. They should draw closer to closer to God. God had plans for them as agents of change and development.”